getSeedData

protected abstract List<ReportRow> getSeedData()
Returns seed data for the report. These rows have enough key data to populate the whole report with additional queries. The final row count may expand beyond this list (see {#fillRow}).

fillRow

protected abstract List<ReportRow> fillRow(ReportRow seededRow)
Fills a report row with remaining data (that was not part of, but is queried by the seed data). There may be cases where a single row of seed data will expand into multiple rows of filled data, thus the return type of list. However, the returned set of rows should only represent the key data in the seed row. In most cases, this list will only contain the initial row.

Use ReportRow.setSubIndex() to specify the render order if the returned list has multiple rows.

You may want to clone the seed row to keep memory footprint low since all seed rows are in memory for the duration of the report run. Cloning also makes sense if you're rows may multiply.

run

public void run()
         throws IOException
Since the renderer is associated with a single output stream, DO NOT call this method more than once per object without first setting a new renderer.
